# Frontend Conventions

## Stack
- Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS ‚Äî no framework (no React, Vue, etc.)
- Server-rendered via Express `res.sendFile()` from `views/`
- Stripe.js for payment forms, client-side fetch for API calls

## Structure
- `views/` ‚Äî full HTML pages (dashboard, checkout, login, store, shipping, etc.)
- `views/admin/` ‚Äî admin panel pages
- `public/` ‚Äî static assets (images, CSS, client JS)
- Inline `<script>` blocks in HTML files handle page-specific logic

## Patterns
- API calls use `fetch()` with `credentials: 'include'` for session cookies
- Cart state managed client-side in `sessionStorage` (keys: `cart`, `shippingAddress`, `shippingCost`)
- Shipping address forms post JSON to `/api/save-shipping-address`
- Checkout flow: store ‚Üí addons ‚Üí shipping ‚Üí checkout ‚Üí thankyou
- Backer flow starts at login (PIN or email OTP) ‚Üí dashboard

## Cart & sessionStorage
- `sessionStorage.cart` only contains items the user actively added (platform add-ons, pledge upgrades)
- Paid backers' KS pledge and KS add-ons are NOT in sessionStorage ‚Äî they are display-only
- Dropped backers' pledge + KS addons ARE in sessionStorage (added by dashboard.html at backer prices)
- `shipping.html` injects pledge + KS addons into a local cart copy before calling `/api/calculate-shipping`
- Server-side `/api/create-payment-intent` also injects pledge + KS addons into the order record

## Duplicate Order Prevention
- checkout, shipping, addons, store pages all check `/api/user/completed-order` on load
- If completed order exists: clear sessionStorage cart and redirect to `/dashboard`
- checkout.html also handles browser back-button via `pageshow` event (bfcache restore)
- Backend rejects checkout if order already has `card_saved`/`succeeded`/`charged`/`charge_failed` status

## KS Items Display
- `addons.html` shows KS pledge and KS addons with "Paid" badge ‚Äî purely visual, NOT in cart
- `dashboard.html` shows KS items in the completed order view or as informational display
- KS addon key mapping: `pendant` ‚Üí "Flitt Locust Pendant", `audiobook_addon` ‚Üí "MAYA: Seed Takes Root Audiobook", `built_env_addon` ‚Üí "Built Environments of MAYA Hardcover", `lorebook_addon` ‚Üí "MAYA Lorebook"

## UI/UX
- Modern, clean design with consistent color palette
- Responsive layouts using CSS flexbox/grid
- Toast notifications for user feedback
- Loading states on buttons during async operations
- Form validation both client-side (required fields) and server-side

## Key Pages
- `dashboard.html` ‚Äî backer hub showing pledge, addons, order status, shipping
- `checkout.html` ‚Äî Stripe Elements card form, order summary, price breakdown
- `store.html` ‚Äî product catalog with add-to-cart
- `shipping.html` ‚Äî address form, shipping calculation (injects KS items locally before API call)
- `addons.html` ‚Äî cart review page showing KS items (display-only) + platform cart items
- `login.html` ‚Äî PIN entry or email OTP for backer auth
- `thankyou.html` ‚Äî order confirmation with "Go to Dashboard" CTA
- `admin/` ‚Äî admin panel for managing orders, users, and analytics
